
[1]venomous

   VEN'OMOUS, a.

   1. Poisonous; noxious to animal life; as, the bite of a serpent may be
   venomous. The sack at the base of the rattlesnake's teeth, contains
   venomous matter.

   2. Noxious; mischievous; malignant; as a venomous progeny.

   3. Spiteful; as a venomous writer.
